# Smithy type naming in Rust

When Smithy-generated types and application/domain types share the same names (e.g. `CatalogItem`, `Category`):

- **Refer to Smithy types by renaming the parent module, not the type.** Keep service/domain types under their original names; disambiguate only the Smithy side via the module path.
- **Apply this only when there are name conflicts.** If there is no clash, use types directly without aliasing.

**Good:** alias the parent module and use type names as-is with a module prefix for Smithy:

```rust
use catalog_api::model as smithy;
use catalog_api::types as smithy_types;
use catalog_svc::catalog::api::{CatalogItem, Category};

fn map_category_from_smithy(value: smithy::Category) -> Category { ... }
fn to_smithy(value: CatalogItem) -> smithy::CatalogItem { ... }
```

**Avoid:** renaming the types themselves (e.g. `SmithyCatalogItem`, `ServiceCategory`).
